---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: Style Gallery
description: A curated library of design systems showcasing different aesthetic approaches and style guides.
---

<section class="py-12 md:py-16 lg:py-20">
  <div style="max-width: 1440px; margin: 0 auto; padding-left: var(--swiss-grid-margin); padding-right: var(--swiss-grid-margin);">
    {# Swiss header - asymmetric with section number #}
    <div class="swiss-grid mb-12" style="border-left: 4px solid var(--swiss-red); padding-left: var(--space-md);">
      <div class="swiss-col-7">
        <p class="text-sm font-bold uppercase tracking-wider mb-2" style="color: var(--swiss-gray-600);">03 — STYLE GALLERY</p>
        <h1 class="font-bold mb-4" style="font-size: var(--fluid-h1); line-height: 1.1; letter-spacing: -0.02em;">{{ title }}</h1>
        <p class="text-lg mb-4" style="color: var(--swiss-gray-700); max-width: 60ch;">{{ description }}</p>
        <p style="color: var(--swiss-gray-600); max-width: 60ch;">This page is dedicated to being a library for style galleries, showcasing various design approaches and aesthetic philosophies.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    {# Structural divider #}
    <div class="swiss-divider mb-16"></div>

    {# Style Gallery Cards #}
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="swiss-grid mb-8">
        <div class="swiss-col-12">
          <h2 class="font-bold mb-2" style="font-size: var(--fluid-h3);">Design Systems</h2>
          <p style="color: var(--swiss-gray-700);">Explore different aesthetic approaches and their visual languages.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(350px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem;">
        {# Nordic Minimalism Card #}
        <article style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--swiss-gray-300); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); transition: all 0.3s ease;">
          <div style="height: 200px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8fafc 0%, #e2e8f0 100%); position: relative;">
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 1.5rem; left: 1.5rem; width: 60px; height: 60px; background: #ffffff; border-radius: 50%; box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);"></div>
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: 1.5rem; right: 1.5rem; width: 40px; height: 40px; background: #64748b; border-radius: 4px;"></div>
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: 1.5rem; left: 1.5rem; width: 80px; height: 4px; background: #cbd5e1; border-radius: 2px;"></div>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 2rem;">
            <h3 style="font-weight: bold; margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0; color: var(--swiss-black); font-size: 1.25rem;">Nordic Minimalism</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0; color: var(--swiss-gray-700); line-height: 1.6;">Clean, functional design inspired by Scandinavian aesthetics. Emphasizes whitespace, natural materials, and purposeful simplicity.</p>
            <a href="/blog/nordic-minimalism/" class="btn-swiss-primary" style="text-decoration: none;">Explore Style →</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        {# Neo Brutalism Card #}
        <article style="background: white; border: 1px solid var(--swiss-gray-300); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08); transition: all 0.3s ease;">
          <div style="height: 200px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1a1a 0%, #404040 100%); position: relative;">
            <div style="position: absolute; top: 1.5rem; left: 1.5rem; width: 80px; height: 20px; background: #ff0000; transform: rotate(-2deg);"></div>
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: 1.5rem; right: 1.5rem; width: 60px; height: 60px; background: #ffff00; border: 3px solid #000000; transform: rotate(5deg);"></div>
            <div style="position: absolute; bottom: 1.5rem; left: 1.5rem; width: 100px; height: 8px; background: #ffffff; box-shadow: 2px 2px 0 #000000;"></div>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 2rem;">
            <h3 style="font-weight: bold; margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0; color: var(--swiss-black); font-size: 1.25rem;">Neo Brutalism</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0; color: var(--swiss-gray-700); line-height: 1.6;">Bold, raw design with stark contrasts, geometric shapes, and unapologetic visual weight. Digital brutalism for the modern web.</p>
            <a href="/blog/neo-brutalism/" class="btn-swiss-primary" style="text-decoration: none;">Explore Style →</a>
          </div>
        </article>

        {# Third Style Placeholder Card #}
        <article style="background: white; border: 2px dashed var(--swiss-gray-300); border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; transition: all 0.3s ease;">
          <div style="height: 200px; background: repeating-linear-gradient(45deg, #f8fafc 0px, #f8fafc 10px, #f1f5f9 10px, #f1f5f9 20px); position: relative; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
            <div style="width: 60px; height: 60px; border: 2px dashed var(--swiss-gray-400); border-radius: 50%; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;">
              <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: var(--swiss-gray-500);">+</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div style="padding: 2rem;">
            <h3 style="font-weight: bold; margin: 0 0 0.75rem 0; color: var(--swiss-black); font-size: 1.25rem;">Coming Soon</h3>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0; color: var(--swiss-gray-700); line-height: 1.6;">New design system in development. Stay tuned for another unique aesthetic approach to inspire your projects.</p>
            <button class="btn-swiss" disabled style="opacity: 0.5; cursor: not-allowed;">In Development</button>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    {# Submission Section #}
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="swiss-grid">
        <div class="swiss-col-8 swiss-col-start-3" style="text-align: center;">
          <div style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f8fafc 0%, #f1f5f9 100%); border: 1px solid var(--swiss-gray-300); border-radius: 12px; padding: 3rem 2rem; box-shadow: 0 4px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
            <h2 style="font-weight: bold; margin: 0 0 1rem 0; color: var(--swiss-black); font-size: var(--fluid-h3);">Share Your Style</h2>
            <p style="margin: 0 0 2rem 0; color: var(--swiss-gray-700); line-height: 1.6; max-width: 50ch; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
              Have a unique design system or aesthetic approach you'd like to showcase? Submit your style guide to be featured in our library.
            </p>
            <a href="/blog/submit-style-guide/" class="btn-swiss-primary" style="text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem;">
              <span>Submit Style Guide</span>
              <span style="font-size: 1.2em;">→</span>
            </a>
            <p style="margin: 1.5rem 0 0 0; color: var(--swiss-gray-600); font-size: 0.875rem;">
              Include examples, color palettes, typography, and component specifications
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</section>
